post_text: We are excited to announce that the USDA along with KDHE has approved all students as FREE for school meals!! There is no charge for any students at this time. This program will continue through December 2020 or until Federal money is no longer available, whichever is sooner. This program is available to all schools through the Summer Food Service Program. This would be a great time to encourage your child(ren) to try school meals!!

Week of August 31st through September 5th

Tuesday, September 1st, HS Volleyball game at Caney
Masks will be required and temps will be taken. Temps above 100.4 will not be allowed to enter. No concession stand will be available at the game. There is no limit to the number of fans allowed at the vball game at this time.

Thursday, Sept. 3rd, MS and HS volleyball at Home. MS Football is postponed. HS volleyball will be in the main gym. Temperatures will be taken, and masks will be required. MS volleyball will be in the West gym. Temperatures will be taken, and masks will be required for all attendees. Each MS volleyball player is allowed 2 tickets for purchase, and we will have 32 extra tickets available to purchase at the door on a first come first serve basis.

Friday, September 4th, HS football is at home vs. Sedan. No limit to the crowd but all must wear masks upon entry and where social distancing can not be maintained such as concession stand lines, restrooms, etc.

We will make our best effort to live stream all games on Facebook Live. Stay tuned for details!

MS/HS – sign up in the office if you would like to make changes to your 1st semester schedule. Monday is the last day to sign up!

Juniors: If you want your Biology notebook or plant collection from last year, please stop by Ms. Swafford's room to pick it up ASAP. If you haven't' picked it up by Sept. 1, it will be discarded.

Scripts for the Fall Play, A Little Princess, may be checked out in Mrs. McCreight’s room with Mrs. McCreight. She will sign your name on the clip board and hand you a script. Auditions will be Saturday, September 5th from 9 AM to Noon. There are many excellent roles to play, so read the script to decide if you would like to be a part of this Production! All actors will not need to be present at every rehearsal.

Flinthills Booster Club
August 23 at 3:38 AM ·

Flinthills Booster Club will meet Monday August 24th at 6:00 pm in the high school commons. The booster club supports extracurricular activities during the year such as TSA, Forensics, Scholars Bowl, and the different sports teams. Patron participation in booster club activities has been declining in recent years. It is important for us to get new ideas and more people supporting the booster clubs efforts if it is going to be able to continue the student support as in past years. There are many different ways to be involved we hope to see you at the meeting to discuss those possibilities.

Parents,
We have made some changes to Open House/ Meet your teacher night. In order to limit the amount of traffic in the building we are using signup genius to schedule your time to meet with our staff. We ask that you wear a mask when entering the building until you have your temperature taken. Middle and High School parents enter the main entrance to the High School and Intermediate parents enter the north entrance. Primary parents enter through the main entrance. We have extended the time for meet your teacher to 1:00 pm to 7:00 pm. Here is the link to sign up for time: https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0D4CA9AC29A5F8C43-open
Find your child's teacher or grade and sign up to bring your back to school supplies.
Please feel free to call me if you have any questions,
Mr. Gawith

SAFE students (and anyone else interested!)
DCCCA Prevention Services is offering Opioid Prevention Training specifically for youth. Middle school and high school youth are invited to participate. Teens will engage in discussion about how opioids can impact both the body and brain, about the dangers of misuse and the important fact that anyone can become addicted. Each session will repeat the same content, so students only need to attend once to receive a certificate.

SAFE students (and anyone else interested!)
DCCCA Prevention Services is offering Opioid Prevention Training specifically for youth. Middle school and high school youth are invited to participate. Teens will engage in discussion about how opioids can impact both the body and brain, about the dangers of misuse and the important fact that anyone can become addicted. Each session will repeat the same content, so students only need to attend once to receive a certificate.

Registration is open now!

post_text: All Kansas School Districts were just informed by the Kansas State Commissioner of Education that any in-person graduation/promotion (including drive-up/drive-in) are prohibited until at least May 18th. It will be announced by the Governor this afternoon. This means that Pre-K graduation for tonight is canceled/postponed. 8th Grade Promotion/Senior Graduation is canceled on May 16th and will be rescheduled to a later date. We will notify you as soon as we know how and when we can proceed. We apologize for these inconveniences, but we are under direct orders. Thank you.

post_text:
Driver Education
Hello this is to inform you that the driver education class will still be held this year starting this Thursday April 2nd, 2020. The class will be on line until May 21st. The driving will begin after that, If the groups are not lifted we will only be in groups of 4, so we will be safe. I need some things emailed from you if you intend to take DR.ED.
1. Your first and last legal name
2. Your email, school preferably.
I need these by Wednesday, April 1st @ 6:00pm if you are intending on taking the class. We will then meet on Thursday, April 2nd at the main doors of the school @ 6:00pm to 7:00pm so I can make sure you are able to log into the system to complete the modules. post_text: If we are delivering food to your home, please find a cooler, big enough to hold all your meals, and set it by your front door. The drivers will honk when they pull in the drive and then deliver your meals into that cooler. Once they leave, you can go and retrieve. Please keep the cooler sanitized and clean. This is for everyone's safety. It will limit our person to person contact and hopefully be beneficial in keeping everyone healthy! Stay safe Mustangs! We miss you!

Dear Flinthills Community,
In anticipation that school may be closed into next week and beyond due to the COVID-19/Coronavirus, we are considering the possibility of continuing to provide meals (lunch and/or breakfast). If you need the school to provide meals, please email Jeremy Boldra at j.boldra@usd492.org and indicate whether you would take advantage of lunch and/or breakfast. Please be specific as to whether you would like lunch and whether you would like breakfast or both. This will help give us an accurate count as to what needs are out there so we can better serve the needs of our school community.
Thank you,
Jeremy Boldra
